@RootFlow.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5011
@conversationId = REPLACE_WITH_CONVERSATION_ID

GET {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/
Accept: application/json

###

GET {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/health
Accept: application/json

###

POST {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/api/documents
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=RootFlowBoundary

--RootFlowBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="rootflow-smoke.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

RootFlow helps businesses answer questions from internal knowledge.
It stores uploaded content, retrieves relevant context, and returns grounded responses.
--RootFlowBoundary--

###

GET {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/api/documents
Accept: application/json

###

POST {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/api/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "How does RootFlow answer questions?",
  "maxContextChunks": 3
}

###

# Replace @conversationId with the value returned from POST /api/chat.
GET {{RootFlow.Api_HostAddress}}/api/conversations/{{conversationId}}
Accept: application/json

###
